From: ShapeWorks build_dependencies.sh
Subject: Fix Approximate3DNormals() legacy wrapper to call the method

Upstream's legacy SurfaceSpatialObject<>::Approximate3DNormals() wrapper does
`return ComputeNormals;` — but in current ITK that name resolves to the
ComputeNormals() member function (`bool (...)()`), not a member variable, and
the compiler fails the bool conversion. This only fires under
ITK_WRAPPING=ON + ITK_LEGACY_REMOVE=OFF (the combination
Support/itk-5.4-legacy-remove.patch enables), because upstream's
cmake_dependent_option normally forces LEGACY_REMOVE on when wrapping is on,
so this legacy code path never gets compiled in the upstream-tested config.
Fix: forward the call (`return this->ComputeNormals();`) so the wrapper
actually wraps.
---
 Modules/Core/SpatialObjects/include/itkSurfaceSpatialObject.hxx | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Modules/Core/SpatialObjects/include/itkSurfaceSpatialObject.hxx b/Modules/Core/SpatialObjects/include/itkSurfaceSpatialObject.hxx
index abc123..def456 100644
--- a/Modules/Core/SpatialObjects/include/itkSurfaceSpatialObject.hxx
+++ b/Modules/Core/SpatialObjects/include/itkSurfaceSpatialObject.hxx
@@ -70,7 +70,7 @@ template <unsigned int TDimension, typename TSurfacePointType>
 bool
 SurfaceSpatialObject<TDimension, TSurfacePointType>::Approximate3DNormals()
 {
-  return ComputeNormals;
+  return this->ComputeNormals();
 }
 #endif // LEGACY

